net: Move MII out from under NET_CORE and hide it

jira LE-1907
Rebuild_History Non-Buildable kernel-3.10.0-514.el7
commit-author Ben Hutchings <ben@decadent.org.uk>
commit a1606c7dc64d8449676d7e840dd2cd0c4e0a0c57
Empty-Commit: Cherry-Pick Conflicts during history rebuild.
Will be included in final tarball splat. Ref for failed cherry-pick at:
ciq/ciq_backports/kernel-3.10.0-514.el7/a1606c7d.failed

All drivers that select MII also need to select NET_CORE because MII
depends on it.  This is a bit ridiculous because NET_CORE is just a
menu option that doesn't enable any code by itself.

There is also no need for it to be a visible option, since its users
all select it.

	Signed-off-by: Ben Hutchings <ben@decadent.org.uk>
	Acked-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
	Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
(cherry picked from commit a1606c7dc64d8449676d7e840dd2cd0c4e0a0c57)
	Signed-off-by: Jonathan Maple <jmaple@ciq.com>

